ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This course is awesome. It is a very good introduction to welding and we learned a couple of extra skills like soldering and cutting with oxy-acetylene torches.
Yes, if you want to learn how to work with metals and build things in a shop, this is a great course.
I would definitely recommend this section for another TD&P Drama student.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This course will be extremely helpful when I need to build test articles in the future.
It was a great change of pace from my normal courseload and gave me a chance to experience and learn things out of the typical school of drama curriculum.
